- "vast sea of research" is a metaphorical expression for the extensive field of research endeavors;
- "identity of the models" refers to the unique identifiers allocated to each model, "model_id";
- "average grades" refer to the average scores given to the models, calculated based on the evaluation metric.

sql:
SELECT model_id, MAX(score) AS highest_score
FROM model_evaluations
GROUP BY model_id;

SELECT researchers.researcher_name, researcher_model_evaluations.score
FROM researchers
INNER JOIN researcher_model_evaluations ON researchers.researcher_id = researcher_model_evaluations.researcher_id;

